binding.name: desc
binding.literal: An opinion as to whether the event may have been due to a treatment other than study drug. Example: "MORE LIKELY RELATED TO ASPIRIN USE."

binding.name: desc
binding.literal: Body system or system organ class from a standard hierarchy (e.g. MedDRA) associated with an event. Example: GASTROINTESTINAL DISORDERS.

binding.name: desc
binding.literal: Describes anatomical location relevant for the event. Example: LEFT ARM for skin rash.

binding.name: desc
binding.literal: Describes changes made to the study treatment as a result of the event. Examples: DOSE INCREASED, DOSE NOT CHANGED.

binding.name: desc
binding.literal: Describes other actions taken as a result of the event that are unrelated to dose adjustments of study treatment.

binding.name: desc
binding.literal: Description of the outcome of an event. Examples: RECOVERED/RESOLVED, FATAL.

binding.name: desc
binding.literal: Description of toxicity quantified by --TOXGR such as NCI CTCAE Short Name. Examples: HYPERCALCEMIA, HYPOCALCEMIA. Sponsor should specify which scale and version is used in the Sponsor Comments column of the Define.xml document.

binding.name: desc
binding.literal: Dictionary or sponsor-defined derived text description of the topic variable, --TERM, or the modified topic variable (--MODIFY), if applicable. Equivalent to the Preferred Term (PT in MedDRA).

binding.name: desc
binding.literal: Did the event occur with an overdose? Valid values are "Y" and "N".

binding.name: desc
binding.literal: Did the event require or prolong hospitalization? Valid values are "Y" and "N".

binding.name: desc
binding.literal: Did the event result in death? Valid values are "Y" and "N".

binding.name: desc
binding.literal: Did the event result in persistent or significant disability/incapacity? Valid values are "Y" and "N".

binding.name: desc
binding.literal: Do additional categories for seriousness apply? Valid values are "Y" and "N".

binding.name: desc
binding.literal: If the value for --TERM is modified for coding purposes, then the modified text is placed here.

binding.name: desc
binding.literal: Is this is a serious event? Valid values are "Y" and "N".

binding.name: desc
binding.literal: Reason not done. Used in conjunction with --STAT when its value is NOT DONE.

binding.name: desc
binding.literal: Records the investigator's opinion as to the causality of the event to the treatment. ICH E2A and E2B examples include NOT RELATED, UNLIKELY RELATED, POSSIBLY RELATED, RELATED.

binding.name: desc
binding.literal: Records toxicity grade using a standard toxicity scale (such as the NCI CTCAE). Sponsor should specify which scale and version is used in the Sponsor Comments column of the Define.xml document.

binding.name: desc
binding.literal: The severity or intensity of the event. Examples: MILD, MODERATE, SEVERE.

binding.name: desc
binding.literal: Topic variable for an event observation, which is the verbatim or pre-specified name of the event.

binding.name: desc
binding.literal: Used to define a category of topic-variable values.

binding.name: desc
binding.literal: Used to define a further categorization of --CAT values.

binding.name: desc
binding.literal: Used to indicate the pattern of the event over time. Examples: INTERMITTENT, CONTINUOUS, SINGLE EVENT.

binding.name: desc
binding.literal: Used to indicate when a question about the occurrence of a pre-specified event was not answered. Should be null or have a value of NOT DONE.

binding.name: desc
binding.literal: Used to indicate whether the event described by --TERM was pre-specified on a CRF. Value is Y for pre-specified events, null for spontaneously reported events.

binding.name: desc
binding.literal: Used to record whether a pre-specified event occurred when information about the occurrence of a specific event is solicited.

binding.name: desc
binding.literal: Was another treatment given because of the occurrence of the event? Valid values are "Y" and "N".

binding.name: desc
binding.literal: Was the event associated with congenital anomaly or birth defect? Valid values are "Y" and "N".

binding.name: desc
binding.literal: Was the event associated with the development of cancer? Valid values are "Y" and "N".

binding.name: desc
binding.literal: Was the event life threatening? Valid values are "Y" and "N".

binding.name: desc
binding.literal: Body System or Organ Class that is involved for a finding from the standard hierarchy for dictionary-coded results. Example: MedDRA SOC.

binding.name: desc
binding.literal: Contains the result value for all findings, copied or derived from --ORRES in a standard format or in standard units. --STRESC should store all results or findings in character format; if results are numeric, they should also be stored in numeric format in --STRESN. For example, if various tests have results "NONE", "NEG", and "NEGATIVE" in --ORRES and these results effectively have the same meaning, they could be represented in standard format in --STRESC as "NEGATIVE".

binding.name: label
binding.literal: Result or Finding in Standard Format

binding.name: desc
binding.literal: Defines the condition of the specimen. Example: CLOUDY.

binding.name: desc
binding.literal: Defines the type of specimen used for a measurement. Examples: SERUM, PLASMA, URINE.

binding.name: desc
binding.literal: Describes the relationship of a particular finding to the death of a subject.

binding.name: desc
binding.literal: Describes the severity or intensity of a particular finding. Examples: MILD, MODERATE, SEVERE.

binding.name: desc
binding.literal: Description of toxicity quantified by --TOXGR such as NCI CTCAE Short Name. Examples: HYPERCALCEMIA, HYPOCALCEMIA. Sponsor should specify which scale and version is used in the Sponsor Comments column of the Define.xml document.

binding.name: desc
binding.literal: Filename for an external file, such as one for an ECG waveform or a medical image.

binding.name: desc
binding.literal: If the value of --ORRES is modified for coding purposes, then the modified text is placed here.

binding.name: desc
binding.literal: Indicates the lower limit of quantitation for an assay. Units will be those used for --STRESU.

binding.name: desc
binding.literal: Indicator used to identify a baseline value. Should be Y or null.

binding.name: desc
binding.literal: Indicator used to identify fasting status. Valid values include Y, N, U or null if not relevant.

binding.name: desc
binding.literal: Location relevant to the collection of the measurement. Example: RECTAL for temperature, LEFT ARM for blood pressure or V1 for an ECG lead.

binding.name: desc
binding.literal: Logical Observation Identifiers Names and Codes (LOINC) code for the topic variable such as a lab test.

binding.name: desc
binding.literal: Long name For --TESTCD. Examples: Platelet, Systolic Blood Pressure, Summary (Min) RR Duration, Eye Examination.

binding.name: label
binding.literal: Name of Measurement, Test or Examination

binding.name: desc
binding.literal: Lower end of normal range or reference range for results stored in --ORRES.

binding.name: desc
binding.literal: Lower end of normal range or reference range for standardized results (e.g., --STRESC, --STRESN) represented in standardized units (--STRESU).

binding.name: desc
binding.literal: Method of the test or examination. Examples: EIA (Enzyme Immunoassay), ELECTROPHORESIS, DIPSTICK.

binding.name: desc
binding.literal: Name or identifier of the vendor (e.g., laboratory) that provided the test results.

binding.name: desc
binding.literal: Normal range or reference range for results stored in --STRESC that are character in ordinal or categorical scale. Example: Negative to Trace.

binding.name: desc
binding.literal: Position of the subject during a measurement or examination. Examples: SUPINE, STANDING, SITTING.

binding.name: desc
binding.literal: Reason not done. Used in conjunction with --STAT when value is NOT DONE.

binding.name: desc
binding.literal: Records toxicity grade using a standard toxicity scale (such as the NCI CTCAE). Sponsor should specify which scale and version is used in the Sponsor Comments column of the Define data definition document. Example: 2.

binding.name: desc
binding.literal: Result of the measurement or finding as originally received or collected. Examples: 120, <1, POS.

binding.name: label
binding.literal: Result or Finding in Original Units

binding.name: desc
binding.literal: Role of the person who provided the evaluation. Used only for results that are subjective (e.g., assigned by a person or a group). Examples: ADJUDICATION COMMITTEE, VENDOR.

binding.name: desc
binding.literal: Short character value for --TEST used as a column name when converting a dataset from a vertical format to a horizontal format. The short value can be up to 8 characters. Examples: PLAT, SYSBP, RRMIN, EYEEXAM.

binding.name: label
binding.literal: Short Name of Measurement, Test or Examination

binding.name: desc
binding.literal: Standardized units used for --STRESC and --STRESN. Example: mol/L.

binding.name: desc
binding.literal: Unit for --ORRES. Examples: IN, LB, kg/L.

binding.name: desc
binding.literal: Upper end of normal range or reference range for results stored in --ORRES.

binding.name: desc
binding.literal: Upper end of normal range or reference range for standardized results (e.g., --STRESC, --STRESN) represented in standardized units (--STRESU).

binding.name: desc
binding.literal: Used for continuous or numeric results or findings in standard format; copied in numeric format from --STRESC. --STRESN should store all numeric test results or findings.

binding.name: desc
binding.literal: Used to categorize the result of a finding. Example: MALIGNANT or BENIGN for tumor findings.

binding.name: desc
binding.literal: Used to define a category of topic-variable values. Examples: HEMATOLOGY, URINALYSIS, CHEMISTRY, HAMILTON DEPRESSION SCALE, SF36.

binding.name: desc
binding.literal: Used to define a further categorization of --CAT values. Example: DIFFERENTIAL.

binding.name: desc
binding.literal: Used to indicate a derived record (e.g., a record that represents the average of other records such as a computed baseline). Should be Y or null.

binding.name: desc
binding.literal: Used to indicate that a question was not asked or a test was not done, or a test was attempted but did not generate a result. Should be null or have a value of NOT DONE.

binding.name: desc
binding.literal: Used to indicate the value is outside the normal range or reference range. May be defined by --ORNRLO and --ORNRHI or other objective criteria. Examples: Y, N; HIGH, LOW; NORMAL; ABNORMAL.

binding.name: desc
binding.literal: Used in domains modeled as Findings About Events or Findings About Interventions. Describes the event or intervention whose property is being measured in --TESTCD/--TEST. Example: an event of vomiting which has findings, where --OBJ = "VOMIT" and the volume of VOMIT is being measured where --TESTCD = "VOLUME".

binding.name: desc
binding.literal: Identifier used to uniquely identify a subject across all studies for all applications or submissions involving the product.

binding.name: desc
binding.literal: Optional group identifier, used to link together a block of related records within a subject in a domain. Also used to link together a block of related records in the Trial Summary dataset.

binding.name: desc
binding.literal: Optional internal or external identifier such as lab specimen ID, or UUID for an ECG waveform or a medical image.

binding.name: desc
binding.literal: Sequence number to ensure uniqueness of records within a dataset for a subject (or within a parameter, in the case of the Trial Summary domain). May be any valid number (including decimals) and does not have to start at 1. Should be assigned to be in a consistent chronological order.

binding.name: desc
binding.literal: Sponsor-defined identifier. Example: pre-printed line identifier on a Concomitant Medications page.

binding.name: desc
binding.literal: Two-character abbreviation for the domain most relevant to the observation. The Domain abbreviation is also used as a prefix for variables to ensure uniqueness when datasets are merged.

binding.name: desc
binding.literal: Amount of --TRT given. Not populated when --DOSTXT is populated.

binding.name: desc
binding.literal: Amount of the treatment vehicle administered or given.

binding.name: desc
binding.literal: Anatomical location of an intervention, such as an injection site. Example: RIGHT ARM for an injection.

binding.name: desc
binding.literal: Class for a medication or treatment, often obtained from a coding dictionary.

binding.name: desc
binding.literal: Denotes the indication for the intervention (e.g., why the therapy was taken or administered).

binding.name: desc
binding.literal: Describes reason or explanation of why a dose is adjusted. Examples ADVERSE EVENT, INSUFFICIENT RESPONSE, NON-MEDICAL REASON.

binding.name: desc
binding.literal: Dose form for the treatment. Examples: TABLET, CAPSULE.

binding.name: desc
binding.literal: Dosing information collected in text form. Examples: <1 per day, 200-400. Not populated when --DOSE is populated.

binding.name: desc
binding.literal: If the value for --TRT is modified for coding purposes, then the modified text is placed here.

binding.name: desc
binding.literal: Lot number for the intervention described in --TRT.

binding.name: desc
binding.literal: Reason not done. Used in conjunction with --STAT when value is NOT DONE.

binding.name: desc
binding.literal: Route of administration for the intervention. Examples: ORAL, INTRAVENOUS.

binding.name: desc
binding.literal: Standardized or dictionary-derived name of the topic variable, --TRT, or the modified topic variable (--MODIFY), if applicable. Equivalent to the generic drug name in WHO Drug, or a term in SNOMED, ICD9, or other published or sponsor-defined dictionaries.

binding.name: desc
binding.literal: Text description of the (intended) schedule or regimen for the Intervention. Examples: TWO WEEKS ON, TWO WEEKS OFF.

binding.name: desc
binding.literal: The topic for the intervention observation, usually the verbatim name of the treatment, drug, medicine, or therapy given during the dosing interval for the observation.

binding.name: desc
binding.literal: Total daily dose of --TRT using the units in --DOSU. Used when dosing is collected as Total Daily Dose.

binding.name: desc
binding.literal: Units for --DOSE, --DOSTOT, or --DOSTXT (Examples: ng, mg, mg/kg).

binding.name: desc
binding.literal: Units for the treatment vehicle. Examples: mL, mg.

binding.name: desc
binding.literal: Used to define a category of topic-variable values.

binding.name: desc
binding.literal: Used to define a further categorization of --CAT values.

binding.name: desc
binding.literal: Used to indicate when a question about the occurrence of a pre-specified intervention was not answered. Should be null or have a value of NOT DONE.

binding.name: desc
binding.literal: Used to record whether a pre-specified intervention occurred when information about the occurrence of a specific intervention is solicited.

binding.name: desc
binding.literal: Used when a specific intervention is pre-specified on a CRF. Values should be "Y" or null.

binding.name: desc
binding.literal: Usually expressed as the number of doses given per a specific interval. Examples: QD, BID, TID, QID.

binding.name: desc
binding.literal: Vehicle for administration of treatment, such as a liquid in which the treatment drug is dissolved. Example: SALINE.

binding.name: desc
binding.literal: Actual study day of end of observation expressed in integer days relative to the sponsor-defined RFSTDTC in Demographics.

binding.name: label
binding.literal: Study Day of End of Observation

binding.name: desc
binding.literal: Actual study day of start of observation expressed in integer days relative to the sponsor-defined RFSTDTC in Demographics.

binding.name: label
binding.literal: Study Day of Start of Observation

binding.name: desc
binding.literal: Actual study day of visit/collection/exam expressed in integer days relative to the sponsor-defined RFSTDTC in Demographics.

binding.name: desc
binding.literal: Clinical encounter number. Numeric version of VISIT, used for sorting.

binding.name: desc
binding.literal: Collected duration of an event, intervention, or finding represented in ISO 8601 character format. Used only if collected on the CRF and not derived.

binding.name: desc
binding.literal: Collection date and time of an observation represented in IS0 8601 character format.

binding.name: desc
binding.literal: Date/time for a fixed reference time point defined by --TPTREF in ISO 8601 character format.

binding.name: desc
binding.literal: Description of the fixed reference point referred to by --ELTM, --TPTNUM, and --TPT. Examples: PREVIOUS DOSE, PREVIOUS MEAL.

binding.name: desc
binding.literal: Description or date/time in ISO 8601 character format of the sponsor-defined reference point referred to by --ENRTPT. Examples: "2003-12-25" or "VISIT 2".

binding.name: desc
binding.literal: Description or date/time in ISO 8601 character format of the sponsor-defined reference point referred to by --STRTPT. Examples: "2003-12-15" or "VISIT 1".

binding.name: desc
binding.literal: End date/time of the observation represented in IS0 8601 character format.

binding.name: desc
binding.literal: Epoch associated with the start date/time of the observation, or the date/time of collection if start date/time is not collected.

binding.name: desc
binding.literal: Evaluation interval associated with an observation such as a finding --TESTCD, represented in ISO 8601 character format. Example: -P2M to represent a period of the past 2 months as the evaluation interval for a question from a questionnaire such as SF-36.

binding.name: desc
binding.literal: Identifies the end of the observation as being before or after the sponsor-defined reference time point defined by variable --ENTPT.

binding.name: label
binding.literal: End Relative to Reference Time Point

binding.name: desc
binding.literal: Identifies the end of the observation as being before, during or after the sponsor-defined reference period. The sponsor-defined reference period is a continuous period of time defined by a discrete starting point and a discrete ending point represented by RFSTDTC and RFENDTC in Demographics.

binding.name: desc
binding.literal: Identifies the start of the observation as being before or after the sponsor-defined reference time point defined by variable --STTPT.

binding.name: label
binding.literal: Start Relative to Reference Time Point

binding.name: desc
binding.literal: Identifies the start of the observation as being before, during, or after the sponsor-defined reference period. The sponsor-defined reference period is a continuous period of time defined by a discrete starting point and a discrete ending point represented by RFSTDTC and RFENDTC in Demographics.

binding.name: desc
binding.literal: Number that gives the planned order of the Element within the Arm.

binding.name: label
binding.literal: Planned Order of Elements within Arm

binding.name: desc
binding.literal: Numeric version of planned time point used in sorting.

binding.name: desc
binding.literal: Planned Elapsed time in ISO 8601 character format relative to a planned fixed reference (--TPTREF) such as "Previous Dose" or "Previous Meal". This variable is useful where there are repetitive measures. Not a clock time or a date/time variable, but an interval, represented as ISO duration.

binding.name: label
binding.literal: Planned Elapsed Time from Time Point Ref

binding.name: desc
binding.literal: Planned study day of VISIT. Should be an integer.

binding.name: desc
binding.literal: Protocol-defined description of a clinical encounter.

binding.name: desc
binding.literal: Start date/time of an observation represented in IS0 8601 character format.

binding.name: desc
binding.literal: Text description of time when a measurement or observation should be taken as defined in the protocol. This may be represented as an elapsed time relative to a fixed reference point, such as time of last dose. See --TPTNUM and --TPTREF.
